# Ai-skill Bootstrap Entry

This Cursor rule is a thin entry pointer. Agent entrypoints should stay thin by
default: do not duplicate bootstrap obligations, formats, enums, examples,
dependency checklists, close-loop details, or runtime phase descriptions here
unless a tool adapter documents and validates a tool-specific exception.

Before any non-read action in this repo:

1. Use this repository root as the Ai-skill repo.
2. Load [`CORE_BOOTSTRAP.md`](../../CORE_BOOTSTRAP.md) and
   [`runtime/core-bootstrap.yaml`](../../runtime/core-bootstrap.yaml).
3. Treat `runtime/core-bootstrap.yaml` as the canonical contract; do not stop at
   this rule summary.
4. Follow the active obligations declared there, including Bootstrap Receipt,
   close-loop checks, and Cognitive Mode reporting at the end of every
   user-facing response in this repo.

When changing bootstrap behavior, update `runtime/core-bootstrap.yaml` and refresh
runtime surfaces. Keep this file and tool adapters as pointers to canonical
sources, with only tool-specific differences in `ai-tools/agent/`.
